First Java Project: Build a Vocabulary Manager
By running this program, the following functions can be realized.
1. Read a list of words (and meanings) from a text file.
2. Display, on screen, a list of all words starting with a particular letter or letters. Also have a way of displaying all words.
3. Display a word, with meaning, at random.
4. Display the meaning of a random word.
5. The word texted by users in the screen will be checked whether the spelling is correct or not.
6. If the word texted by users are wrong, the program is supposed to provide the most likely words that users want to check.
7. Add a word to the list in the text file.
8. Remove a word from the list in the text file.
9. Save all words (and meanings) to a text file.
